The paper proposes a machine learning algorithm based on Brain-inspired Hyperdimensional (HD) computing, which is a subfield of neural networks and artificial intelligence (cs.NE, cs.AR, cs.AI). The focus of the paper is on achieving high energy-efficiency, which is a common concern in hardware implementation of machine learning algorithms (cs.SY). The proposed algorithm also involves stochastic binarization, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning for reducing computational complexity and improving efficiency (cs.LG).
